Description: ALERT - I would like this stay here so that whenever someone searches Accelerated Technologies Holding Corp - ATHC find SCAM activities.
Full Description: Enterprise technology veteran Accelerated Technologies Holding Corps has been offering complete business solutions for some time. is a well-known and "trusted" name in the market for providing business solutions to many. It is a publicly traded company that trades on OTC marketplaces under the ticker $ATHC. While it is far from being one, everything comes together to provide the impression that the organization represents trust, when it doesn't.  Accelerated Technologies Holding Corps is committed to generating a large portion of its income by defrauding gullible people. Given its standing in the market and industry, it may equal blasphemy to many, but ATHC has been stealing for a while now. The information that most people have regarding ATHC is made up- meaning that all that talk about ATHC being a  reliable stock and having a top-notch crew is a lie.   Accelerated Technologies Holding Corps only excels at deceiving and manipulating. The business has years of experience deceiving people and businesses in a variety of inventive ways. You may hear that the  business is growing and introducing new revenue sources, but they are lies engineered by its marketing department. Once you fall for that, it is game over for you and your savings.  As a first hand witness to the scam carried out by its executives, I can testify that ATHC is a sham. The company's team of con artists make it a point to be inventive in their schemes. There is no signature mode of operation, at least not one that I noticed in my interactions with other Accelerated Technologies Holding Corps scam victims. The one error we all made, though, was failing to pay closer attention to the employees' behavior in favor of focusing on the company's flashy outward look. They engineered it so that  I was forced to pay Accelerated Technologies Holding Corps an absurd sum of money because of a contract that I wasn't even aware I had with the business.  I had only sometimes emailed the business for quotes and other concerns. What I believed was just a casual talk turned out to be a weapon for the company to bill me. They managed to do so by sneaking in an offer disguised as an expression that I unknowingly agreed to, and ended up unknowingly bound in a contract. So , pay closer attention to what they communicate if you find yourself in a similar circumstance. Take a minute to look up the company's CEO, Eric Kuvykin and see the data that you pull up.   You'll discover two sets of data:  One being heavily promotional and the second will be truth, sourced from official federal government websites, which will include trial transcripts for cases CEO Kuvykin has been tried in. Eric Kuvykin of Accelerated Technologies Holding Corps is a federally tried scam artist charged with securities fraud and money laundering conspiracy.  So if you need any more proof about all you just read up there, that’s where you should start. Avoid this sham company at all costs!

Popularo is a user driven social news aggregation website launched in February 2008. It is based on the theory that a user should vote for
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Popularo is a user driven social news aggregation website launched in February 2008.  It is based on the theory that a user should vote for the content or topic in question, not for the person that submitted it. After users submit something to Popularo, it becomes available in a random voting box for other users to make a decision about in a "hot or not" style, rapid-fire voting system.  Only the title and headline are displayed in the voting box to help prevent bias or voting fraud. Once a submission receives enough negative votes, it is removed from the system, and once it receives enough positive votes it is promoted to the front page and voting is suspended.  There are no superusers that can sway the vote, every user has an equal vote. The site was launched in 2008 by two guys from Philly that fell in love with digg when it first launched, but like many users became increasingly frustrated with what the site had become.  The more they talked about it, the more they found other people that felt the same way, and Popularo was born.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Other

Description: ONtheAIR is a streaming video platform allowing anyone watching a live stream to video chat with the host in front of the audience.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: ONtheAIR allows anyone who is watching a live stream to video chat with the host in front of the audience. OnTheAir’s streaming video platform powers radio call-in shows for the digital age. A host sets up an OnTheAir show and selects a start time. They receive a unique URL that leads to a landing page with a countdown to their show. OnTheAir lets the host schedule tweets for an hour and a few minutes before the show starts to promote themselves. When the show starts, the host begins live video streaming to the audience. Viewers can text chat with each other and the host, or click a “Call In” button to alert the host that they want to join them “on stage”. The viewer is intelligently walked through an equipment check to turn on their webcam and mic, and shown a preview so they can check their hair. Meanwhile the host can look at the previews of anyone asking to call in, and select who to bring on stage with them for simultaneous, sync’d up video streaming to the audience.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Information Technology, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Messaging and Telecommunications, Music and Audio, Video

Description: New Innovative & Unique Social Network
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Swupa is a very new aesthetically pleasing, innovative "Social Network".  Signing up is just as easy as logging in (just a username/password). Swupa maintains a completely unique look and feel, has a solid easy-to-navigate user interface, and much more. Not only has Swupa implemented the core Social Networking features like friends/requests, user to user messaging, profile picture & user gallery, commenting, posting to your profile and more; but then it separates itself from the competition. Voice messaging, Voice commenting and Voice posts. Swupa utilizes your computer/laptop microphone and allows you to send a voice message to a user, or comment on someones post with a voice comment, or even make a voice post on your profile page or a group you're in with the click of a button. Merge voice comments (Collaborate!); Being the post owner, at any time you can close commenting on that post and merge all voice comments into 1 single playable MP3. So for example you can "Start a story" with your friends via voice comments, where each one of your friends and/or you comment the next word or phrase of the story....then merge and share the finished product! Xbox Live connect & Reddit connect allow you to tie your xbox profile or reddit username to your account, and easily network with those who've done the same. Browse people who play the same games as you, and put a face behind that reddit username as all Reddit Connect's verify that the user is actually who they say they are! Time Spent online: Swupa allows you to privately view how much time exactly (days/hours/minutes/seconds) you have spent on Swupa in total. You can share with your friends how much time you've spent by putting [timespent] in a profile post (only if you want to share!) And much more.
